    <table>
        <tr>
  <th colspan="2"><strong>1.</strong> Match the words with their definition.</th>
    </tr>
  <tr><td>1) compulsory</td><td><strong>A)</strong> able to be used</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2) comprehensive</td><td><strong>B)</strong> a king of education in which pupils of different abilities go to the same school</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3) available</td><td><strong>C)</strong> to go regularly to a certain place</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4) to learn</td><td><strong>D)</strong> must be done because it is the law</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5) to study</td><td><strong>E)</strong> to get the theory of the subject</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6) to attend</td><td><strong>F)</strong> to get some practical skills</td></tr>
  </table>
